      "role": "user",
      "content": "calling it a hallucination feels like a way to shut me down. i'm not seeing things, i'm hearing it. and it's not just random noise. it's too rhythmic. if you look at how frequency modulation works in signal processing, wouldn't it be possible for a high-voltage grid to carry more than just electricity? like a carrier wave for something else?",
